        <name>23.4.2.1 FS expression 1</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
Obtain the Fourier series of \[ f(t) = \lvert t \rvert \hspace{1cm} \pi \leq t \leq \pi \hspace{1cm} f(t + 2\pi) = f(t) \] and use it to calculate the summation \( \displaystyle{\sum _{n = 1}^\infty }\dfrac{1}{(2n - 1)^2} \) by putting \( t = 0\).&lt;p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
\( \displaystyle{ \sum _{n = 1}^\infty } \dfrac{1}{(2n - 1)^2} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>As \( f(t) \) is an even function, \( b_n = 0 \). For \( a_0\) we have
\[ 
\begin{align}
a_0 &amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi} \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^\pi } \lvert t \rvert \hspace{0.1cm} dt \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi}  \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^0 } -t \hspace{0.1cm} dt +  \dfrac{1}{\pi}  \displaystyle{ \int _{0}^\pi } t \hspace{0.1cm} dt \\
&amp;amp;= \pi
\end{align}
\]
By using integration by parts, we then find
\[
\begin{align}
a_n &amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi}  \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^\pi } \lvert t \rvert \cos nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi}  \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^0 } - t \cos nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt + \dfrac{1}{\pi}  \displaystyle{ \int _{0}^\pi }  t \cos nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi} \left( \left[ -\dfrac{t}{n} \sin nt \right]_{-\pi}^0 + \dfrac{1}{n} \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^0 }  \sin nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt + \left[ \dfrac{t}{n} \sin nt \right]_{0}^\pi -  \dfrac{1}{n} \displaystyle{ \int _{0}^\pi }  \sin nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt \right) \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi} \left( \left[ - \dfrac{1}{n^2} \cos nt  \right]_{-\pi}^0 + \left[  \dfrac{1}{n^2} \cos nt \right]_{0}^\pi \right) \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{2}{n^2 \pi} \left( \cos n\pi - 1 \right)
\end{align}
\]
\[ =
\begin{cases}
0 \hspace{1cm} n = 2, 4, 6, \dots \\
-\dfrac{4}{n^2 \pi} \hspace{1cm} n = 1, 3, 5, \dots
\end{cases}
\]
Now rewriting \(n\) to take the form of an odd number as \( 2n - 1\) (where \(n = 1, 2, 3, 4, \dots\)), we have the Fourier series
\[ f(t) = \dfrac{\pi}{2} + \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{-4}{(2n-1)^2\pi} \cos \left[ (2n - 1)t \right] \]
Now setting \(t = 0\) we have \(f(t) = 0\), and therefore
\[ 0 = \dfrac{\pi}{2} +  \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{-4}{(2n-1)^2\pi} \]
which can be rearranged to give
\[  \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{1}{(2n-1)^2} = \dfrac{\pi^2}{8} \]</generalfeedback>
